pageContext.claim: “We actually called up Ukraine. Do you mind if we release it? They said no, they didn't understand why, but they were nice. You know they were very nice. They said you mind, no. We had our Secretary of state call, actually. Do you mind? Because it would be nice to let him know, we're going to release it, right? Would be very nice.”
pageContext.analysis: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky has said he thought only Trump's remarks would be released and said: “I personally think that sometimes such calls between presidents of independent countries should not be published. I just thought that they would publish their part.”
